<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-05T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-05T11:00:00-05:00" n="1108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/6–545: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-05T12:00:00-04:00">June 5,
                                    1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2528. In June 4 Bonnet delivered text of message, dated June 1 but
                            delayed in transmission, from General de Gaulle to the President on the
                            subject of the situation in the Levant. Text follows in separate
                                cable.<note n="13" xml:id="d1108fn13">No. 2549, June 5, 1945, 8
                                p.m., not printed.</note> Please convey the following reply to
                            General de Gaulle in the President’s name: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Through the courtesy of the French Ambassador I have received
                                    your message of June 1 with regard to the situation in the
                                    Levant. I have noted the orders which you have issued to the
                                    French forces there and share your hope that the situation will
                                    now be susceptible of solution by peaceful means.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>